# digit?/ok?/error?/some?/none? are type-specific predicates — calling one
# on a value outside its ADT family must error, not silently answer
# `false` (a wrong-type receiver is a caller bug, not a "no"). Only one
# error per program (it aborts execution), so pick the one most likely to
# regress silently: a String handed to the Char-only `digit?`.
main do
  IO.printLine("hello".digit?)
end
